    "### Math operators\n",
    "\n",
    "Now let's see how we can do various math and logical operations with Python. Here are a few operators that we will be using:\n",
    "\n",
    "* `+` plus\n",
    "* `-` minus\n",
    "* `/` slash\n",
    "* `*` asterisk\n",
    "* `%` percent\n",
    "* `<` less-than\n",
    "* `>` greater-than\n",
    "* `<=` less-than-equal\n",
    "* `>=` greater-than-equal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print \"I will now count my chickens:\"\n",
    "print \"Hens\", 25 + 30 / 6"
